01:27:14.316 --> 01:27:16.840
- When we started. I was
basically a journalist

01:27:16.927 --> 01:27:18.929
trying to start about
extinction of apes.

01:27:20.583 --> 01:27:23.629
It was very easy to
see the consequences

01:27:23.716 --> 01:27:28.721
of this illegal trade in body
parts of chimps and gorillas

01:27:30.767 --> 01:27:35.119
being sold to the rich and the
powerful in Central Africa.

01:27:36.425 --> 01:27:38.688
It was also very easy
to see that the law

01:27:38.775 --> 01:27:41.343
was never enforced because
those that were actually

01:27:41.430 --> 01:27:43.823
behind those trades are
the same police officers

01:27:43.910 --> 01:27:45.477
and wildlife officers
that were in charge

01:27:45.564 --> 01:27:46.957
of applying the law.

01:27:47.044 --> 01:27:49.873
In fact. it was zero
wildlife prosecutions

01:27:49.960 --> 01:27:51.918
for all the time the
law was in place.

01:27:53.746 --> 01:27:57.010
And I went on research
outside of the capital.

01:27:57.097 --> 01:27:59.012
where people were
telling me straight:

01:27:59.099 --> 01:28:02.538
"Hey. we have chimp meat being
sold here and gorilla's meat

01:28:02.625 --> 01:28:05.889
"being sold here. and we
also have two live ones."

01:28:05.976 --> 01:28:07.847
And I said. "What
is this live ones?"

01:28:07.934 --> 01:28:09.632
And these are
basically the survivors

01:28:09.719 --> 01:28:11.895
of the bush meat trade. the
survivors of the killing

01:28:11.982 --> 01:28:13.157
of their entire family.

01:28:14.811 --> 01:28:17.901
So. a poacher can kill
different family of apes.

01:28:17.988 --> 01:28:19.642
family of chimps. let's say.

01:28:19.729 --> 01:28:22.209
Then he would have a baby chimp.

01:28:22.297 --> 01:28:25.038
A baby chimp stays on
the back of its mother

01:28:25.125 --> 01:28:27.084
for the first three
years of his life.

01:28:27.171 --> 01:28:31.393
So if the mother falls from
the tree dead. the baby.

01:28:31.480 --> 01:28:33.917
dependent. doesn't run
away. he just clings

01:28:34.004 --> 01:28:37.616
to the mother's body
and starts crying.

01:28:37.703 --> 01:28:39.488
Poachers will hold in his hand.

01:28:40.619 --> 01:28:42.491
Maybe he could kill
it for the meat on it.

01:28:42.578 --> 01:28:45.102
and sell the meat.
or maybe he can sell.

01:28:45.189 --> 01:28:47.191
or let's try my luck
in the pet trade.

01:28:50.020 --> 01:28:52.414
So. here I was in front of
traffickers who were trying

01:28:52.501 --> 01:28:57.114
to sell me a baby
chimp. abused. tiny.

01:28:57.201 --> 01:29:00.509
one and half years old
baby. about to die.

01:29:01.684 --> 01:29:03.642
I went to the wildlife
station and I said.

01:29:03.729 --> 01:29:05.905
"Listen. apply the law.
there is a baby chimp here

01:29:05.992 --> 01:29:09.344
that can be saved. this
baby chimp can outlive me.

01:29:10.693 --> 01:29:13.957
"So. please let's do something.
let's get the law applied."

01:29:14.044 --> 01:29:16.089
All they wanted was bribes.

01:29:17.700 --> 01:29:19.354
I knew I had to do something.

01:29:19.441 --> 01:29:23.227
Because all of this anger
I had against corruption.

01:29:23.314 --> 01:29:26.143
lack of application of
the law. was right now

01:29:26.230 --> 01:29:29.364
in the face of this baby chimp.

01:29:31.366 --> 01:29:33.629
The following morning
I took a book of law.

01:29:33.716 --> 01:29:36.240
I went to the big house
of these traffickers.

01:29:36.327 --> 01:29:38.895
and I showed them. three
years imprisonment.

01:29:40.157 --> 01:29:41.854
And they were
totally unimpressed.

01:29:43.378 --> 01:29:46.119
And I said. "Well. you know I
know this is nothing for you.

01:29:46.206 --> 01:29:49.688
because with three dollars
bribe you can get away with it."

01:29:51.081 --> 01:29:52.865
Then I started bluffing them.

01:29:52.952 --> 01:29:55.085
And I said. "I am part of this
huge. big international NGO.

01:29:55.172 --> 01:29:57.696
and we are here to
fight corruption.

01:29:57.783 --> 01:29:59.829
to get the law applied.
that's my new job."

01:29:59.916 --> 01:30:01.265
And at that point
they just wanted

01:30:01.352 --> 01:30:03.267
to get rid of the baby chimp.

01:30:03.354 --> 01:30:07.489
I untied him from his ropes.
and I stretched my arms out.

01:30:07.576 --> 01:30:11.144
and he just climbed my body
and gave me one big hug.

01:30:12.581 --> 01:30:17.150
Once I gave him a hug.
he was again transformed.

01:30:18.369 --> 01:30:19.892
back to a baby. a baby
with emotional needs.

01:30:21.981 --> 01:30:25.420
And that hug became
a permanent hug.

01:30:25.507 --> 01:30:28.423
because this baby chimp
basically adopted me.

01:30:29.380 --> 01:30:32.122
[chimp laughing]

01:30:42.828 --> 01:30:45.004
[metal clinking]

01:30:45.091 --> 01:30:47.442
So. I called this
baby chimp 'Future'.

01:30:47.529 --> 01:30:49.226
And I realized at that point.

01:30:49.313 --> 01:30:50.880
that I can actually fight

01:30:50.967 --> 01:30:54.231
not just for a future of
a small. one baby chimp.

01:30:54.318 --> 01:30:55.928
but for the future
of his species.

01:30:56.015 --> 01:30:58.278
We are in the middle of
a fight. a serious fight.

01:30:59.497 --> 01:31:01.412
But I can get a
good night's sleep

01:31:01.499 --> 01:31:04.981
if I know that we got one more
major trafficker behind bars.

01:31:05.068 --> 01:31:06.939
one more official.
corrupt official

01:31:07.026 --> 01:31:08.724
that actually paid
for his crimes.

01:31:15.818 --> 01:31:20.083
- It's commercial gangs.
organized commercial gangs

01:31:20.170 --> 01:31:22.477
of meat poachers.
doing it for profit.

01:31:22.564 --> 01:31:24.479
'cause it's something
for nothing.

01:31:24.566 --> 01:31:26.045
And it's the big cattle barons.

01:31:26.132 --> 01:31:28.526
What you have to remember
about East Africa

01:31:28.613 --> 01:31:30.963
is that it's the Wild West.

01:31:31.050 --> 01:31:33.009
You know. you ever
seen a cowboy movie?

01:31:33.096 --> 01:31:34.793
What's it all about?

01:31:34.880 --> 01:31:37.927
You know. move west. young
man. there's gold down there.

01:31:38.014 --> 01:31:39.972
And in the cowboy
movies you see them.

01:31:40.059 --> 01:31:42.409
With these huge herds of
cattle moving. And in front

01:31:42.497 --> 01:31:46.196
of that stock everything had
to go. Native American tribes.

01:31:46.283 --> 01:31:49.765
wild animals. forests. rivers.
whatever. it was destroyed.

01:31:49.852 --> 01:31:51.549
And that's what's
happening to us.

01:31:54.204 --> 01:31:55.292
- So we're protecting gorillas.

01:31:55.379 --> 01:31:56.598
we're protecting elephants.

01:31:56.685 --> 01:31:57.599
we're trying to
protect orangutans.

01:31:57.686 --> 01:31:59.339
But we're losing.

01:31:59.426 --> 01:32:01.516
Because when we raise money
for NGOs. for organizations

01:32:01.603 --> 01:32:03.953
to support the efforts
of government agencies

01:32:04.040 --> 01:32:06.651
that are trying to
protect these forests.

01:32:06.738 --> 01:32:09.436
We're thinking in terms of
tens. or hundreds of thousands.

01:32:09.524 --> 01:32:11.656
bigger NGOs maybe low millions.

01:32:11.743 --> 01:32:15.442
At the same time corporations
are spending billions

01:32:15.530 --> 01:32:19.316
of dollars to develop
those same lands.

01:32:19.403 --> 01:32:21.623
And the Ministers that
come to our UN meetings

01:32:21.710 --> 01:32:24.887
and sign agreements to protect
apes. are often trumped

01:32:24.974 --> 01:32:27.629
by the more powerful
Ministers of Agriculture

01:32:27.716 --> 01:32:30.153
and Land Development. who
want the mines to develop

01:32:30.240 --> 01:32:31.981
or want the roads to be
put through the forest.

01:32:32.068 --> 01:32:34.940
Even though opening the
forest begins the degradation

01:32:35.027 --> 01:32:37.247
that results in extinction.

01:32:37.334 --> 01:32:40.076
[dramatic music]

01:32:44.428 --> 01:32:46.996
- [Eric] With elephant
tusks and with rhino horns.

01:32:47.083 --> 01:32:50.869
it's a more complicated issue.
it really is. it's a war.

01:32:53.263 --> 01:32:56.527
A place like Kafue is kind
of ground zero in that war.

01:32:56.614 --> 01:32:59.312
And the only way that
the Zambian government

01:32:59.399 --> 01:33:02.359
is going to win that war
is with help from outside

01:33:02.446 --> 01:33:05.362
and with devoting
more resources itself.

01:33:08.626 --> 01:33:10.759
I think it's very positive
that the government

01:33:10.846 --> 01:33:13.762
understands that it has a
crisis and that it needs

01:33:13.849 --> 01:33:15.677
to take drastic
measures to address it.

01:33:15.764 --> 01:33:17.940
And certainly deploying
the Zambian military

01:33:18.027 --> 01:33:21.465
to deal with poaching
would be a drastic measure.

01:33:21.552 --> 01:33:23.772
But it could be that the
situation merits that.

01:33:23.859 --> 01:33:27.776
That it needs to take
such as drastic step.

01:33:28.733 --> 01:33:31.475
[peaceful music]

01:33:45.141 --> 01:33:48.187
- I don't think it's a
question of them not caring

01:33:48.274 --> 01:33:50.189
about the wildlife. I
think it's a question

01:33:50.276 --> 01:33:54.498
of them not knowing what is
going on with their wildlife.

01:33:56.152 --> 01:33:59.634
I'd like to think that as proud
Africans and proud Zambians.

01:33:59.721 --> 01:34:02.158
our life is more
important than money.

01:34:03.942 --> 01:34:06.336
How can we get the
community to be involved

01:34:06.423 --> 01:34:09.992
to benefit from safari hunting?

01:34:10.079 --> 01:34:12.516
So. that they're not
tempted to poach?

01:34:23.048 --> 01:34:28.053
[splashing]
[birds squawking]

01:34:30.665 --> 01:34:34.103
We were sitting at the
camp and I was sitting

01:34:34.190 --> 01:34:38.934
near the radio. and a game
scout radioed in to say

01:34:39.021 --> 01:34:44.026
that he heard four shots. and
of course. the game scouts

01:34:46.419 --> 01:34:50.946
were told to go and
investigate what was happening.

01:34:51.033 --> 01:34:53.470
And the game scouts went
and they spent a night

01:34:53.557 --> 01:34:55.124
in the bush and the
following morning

01:34:55.211 --> 01:34:57.300
they found the elephants.

01:34:57.387 --> 01:34:59.824
And it was a long
weekend. so I think

01:34:59.911 --> 01:35:01.826
that was a Sunday when
the shots were heard.

01:35:01.913 --> 01:35:03.523
the four shots were heard.

01:35:03.610 --> 01:35:06.788
And the Monday morning.
the game scouts reported.

01:35:06.875 --> 01:35:09.312
and we heard over the
radio that it was reported

01:35:09.399 --> 01:35:11.967
that they found
three elephant down.

01:35:12.054 --> 01:35:14.317
And so I jumped into my car

01:35:14.404 --> 01:35:16.972
and I followed the
game scouts to go

01:35:17.059 --> 01:35:18.538
and see what was happening.

01:35:18.625 --> 01:35:21.498
And I took the pictures.
and I was so devastated.

01:35:21.585 --> 01:35:22.847
- [Ranger] So this poor thing

01:35:22.934 --> 01:35:25.241
has been suffering
the whole time?

01:35:28.157 --> 01:35:30.812
[flies buzzing]

01:35:34.641 --> 01:35:37.644
[elephant groaning]

01:35:43.825 --> 01:35:45.565
- I was weeping openly.

01:35:45.652 --> 01:35:47.742
The game scouts were horrified.

01:35:47.829 --> 01:35:50.179
I don't think there was not
one person who stood there.

01:35:50.266 --> 01:35:53.530
including the game scouts.
that didn't drop a tear.

01:35:53.617 --> 01:35:55.662
It was beyond everybody.

01:35:55.750 --> 01:35:57.839
It was so. so sad.

01:35:57.926 --> 01:36:00.363
Especially that she
was a lactating mother.

01:36:00.450 --> 01:36:03.192
She was a lactating mother
with two small babies.

01:36:03.279 --> 01:36:05.020
The tusks were barely that size.

01:36:05.107 --> 01:36:08.066
They killed an elephant
that takes a gestation

01:36:08.153 --> 01:36:11.722
of 18 months and in
another eighteen months

01:36:11.809 --> 01:36:13.942
to make a tusk that size.

01:36:14.029 --> 01:36:16.814
Even the game scouts
were devastated.

01:36:16.901 --> 01:36:19.643
[dramatic music]

01:36:22.951 --> 01:36:26.868
- That is actual slaughter of
an elephant that is put down.

01:36:26.955 --> 01:36:30.175
still alive as the tusk
is carved out of its face.

01:36:30.262 --> 01:36:34.136
Purely so that you can
have a trinket. right?

01:36:34.223 --> 01:36:36.355
It's beautiful artwork.

01:36:36.442 --> 01:36:38.749
This craftsmanship is exquisite.

01:36:38.836 --> 01:36:41.665
but they used a critically
endangered species to do it.

01:36:44.450 --> 01:36:49.455
Wildlife crime is a crime
that is very low risk

01:36:50.326 --> 01:36:51.806
and very high monetary value.

01:36:51.893 --> 01:36:53.459
It's currently estimated

01:36:53.546 --> 01:36:56.027
at a nineteen billion
dollar industry. annually.

01:36:56.114 --> 01:36:59.639
And the fact that the
sentence really is just a slap

01:36:59.726 --> 01:37:01.598
on the wrist for people
that are making millions

01:37:01.685 --> 01:37:04.253
and millions of dollars off
of everybody's wildlife.

01:37:07.691 --> 01:37:10.346
- Well. you know. the sad
thing is they will shoot them

01:37:10.433 --> 01:37:13.044
in the knees to slow
them down or to try

01:37:13.131 --> 01:37:14.785
to stop them from charging.

01:37:14.872 --> 01:37:16.831
You know because this. it's
not likely they're gonna

01:37:16.918 --> 01:37:18.658
get this into the brain. but
they can get it into the legs

01:37:18.745 --> 01:37:20.356
to maybe make them stumble.

01:37:20.443 --> 01:37:22.793
fall and not be able to
charge them or trample them.

01:37:22.880 --> 01:37:24.316
Because it doesn't take much to.

01:37:24.403 --> 01:37:27.798
you know. what does an
elephant weigh. a ton?

01:37:27.885 --> 01:37:29.147
- Eight.
- Eight tons.

01:37:29.234 --> 01:37:30.801
That thing steps on
you. you're dead.

01:37:30.888 --> 01:37:33.717
So. I would imagine
that's probably with an AK

01:37:33.804 --> 01:37:35.545
that's probably their
best effort is to just try

01:37:35.632 --> 01:37:37.852
to shoot the legs
to get 'em to stop.

01:37:37.939 --> 01:37:41.159
And then I don't. from
what I've heard they

01:37:41.246 --> 01:37:43.640
just go up and they just
basically take a machete

01:37:43.727 --> 01:37:46.295
or chainsaw and it's
like. man. I don't.

01:37:46.382 --> 01:37:47.905
How somebody could do something

01:37:47.992 --> 01:37:50.386
like that I just don't know.

01:37:51.953 --> 01:37:53.389
- [Azad] The
animals being driven

01:37:53.476 --> 01:37:55.826
to extinction
affects everything.

01:37:55.913 --> 01:37:57.654
This is a not an
African problem.

01:37:57.741 --> 01:37:59.874
But everyone says" "Poaching
is a problem for Africa."

01:37:59.961 --> 01:38:01.136
No. it's not.

01:38:01.223 --> 01:38:02.137
No. it's not.

01:38:02.224 --> 01:38:03.312
This affects you.

01:38:06.576 --> 01:38:10.928
- [Jane] The current rate
of killing of elephants

01:38:11.015 --> 01:38:14.627
is actually worse
than in the 1980s.

01:38:14.714 --> 01:38:17.456
because the price
of ivory has soared.

01:38:17.543 --> 01:38:18.849
You know so many elephants.

01:38:18.936 --> 01:38:20.372
they're reckoning one elephant

01:38:20.459 --> 01:38:22.679
every 15 minutes across Africa.

01:38:22.766 --> 01:38:25.464
And this is completely
unsustainable.

01:38:25.551 --> 01:38:27.510
So. that some
populations are already

01:38:27.597 --> 01:38:29.512
on the road to extinction.

01:38:29.599 --> 01:38:34.604
And if we don't stop this
terrible poaching soon.

01:38:35.735 --> 01:38:38.869
we may actually lose
this most extraordinary

01:38:38.956 --> 01:38:41.437
and amazing of land mammals.

01:38:47.095 --> 01:38:50.707
- I think we are coming
to a cultural change here.

01:38:50.794 --> 01:38:54.145
One of those changes
is collaboration.

01:38:54.232 --> 01:38:56.408
What we now need to do
is have a Renaissance

01:38:56.495 --> 01:38:59.237
of bringing people
back together.

01:39:08.943 --> 01:39:13.251
[laughs]
[speaking Sangho language]

01:39:13.338 --> 01:39:18.169
We are part of a system
here and not just some being

01:39:18.256 --> 01:39:19.866
that can control nature.

01:39:19.954 --> 01:39:21.520
We can't control nature.

01:39:21.607 --> 01:39:23.305
We're part of nature.

01:40:35.768 --> 01:40:39.381
[somber. mysterious music]
